config BR2_PACKAGE_XONE
	bool "xone"
	depends on BR2_LINUX_KERNEL
	help
	  Out-of-tree GIP (Game Input Protocol) driver for Xbox One and
	  Xbox Series X|S accessories (kernel-module package, P3.2):
	  wired USB controllers/headsets/chatpad, and the Xbox Wireless
	  Dongle (transport/mt76.c talks the dongle's onboard radio
	  directly; it is NOT a Wi-Fi NIC and registers no wiphy).

	  Sourced from dlundqvist/xone, NOT medusalix/xone (the original
	  project) -- medusalix is explicitly in "maintenance mode" (its own
	  README: "will receive only occasional minor fixes", one commit in
	  the 19 months before this pin) and dlundqvist is the README's own
	  named successor, in continuous active development (see xone.mk for
	  the full comparison this project made before picking a fork).

	  FIRMWARE NOTE: the Xbox Wireless Dongle needs
	  /lib/firmware/xow_dongle.bin (and, for this driver, a same-content
	  xone_dongle_<pid>.bin). This package builds and installs the
	  DRIVER MODULES ONLY (unambiguously GPL-2.0-or-later) -- it does
	  NOT fetch, extract, or bundle that firmware itself; see
	  BR2_PACKAGE_XOW_FIRMWARE (package/xow-firmware/) for that, and
	  docs/decisions/0003-xone-firmware.md (Status: Accepted) for the
	  full redistribution analysis this project's maintainer decided.
	  Wired controllers/headsets/chatpad need no firmware at all.

	  https://github.com/dlundqvist/xone

comment "xone needs a Linux kernel to be built"
	depends on !BR2_LINUX_KERNEL
